tionality\",\"title\":\"Wire up metricsRetentionDays to purge old metrics\",\"description\":\"The config already defines metricsRetentionDays (default 365) but no code actually purges old daily_metrics or system_daily_metrics rows. Add a RetentionPolicy for daily_metrics keyed on the date column, and extend runRetention to delete metric rows older than metricsRetentionDays. Register daily_metrics in TABLE_REGISTRY as ephemeral with timestampColumn=date. This prevents unbounded metrics table growth.\",\"reasoning\":\"This is a bug-level gap: the retention config exists but is dead code. daily_metrics rows accumulate forever. Products like Datadog, Prometheus, and Grafana Cloud all enforce metrics retention windows. Without this, disk usage grows linearly with time across all tenants, eventually degrading SQLite performance.\",\"status\":\"pending\",\"user_feedback\":null,\"user_pattern\":0,\"effort\":2,\"impact\":7,\"implemented_at\":null,\"created_at\":\"2026-03-18T18:27:47.329Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-18T18:27:47.329Z\",\"requirement_id\":null,\"goal_id\":null,\"risk\":2,\"provider\":null,\"model\":null,\"detailed\":0}}","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
[2026-03-18T18:27:47.911Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01YCWExaCwkjM2DAYaZ947MJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_014UxABghkrN3Yd1dxQmqqzo","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/ideas \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"scan_id\": \"1482c057-2bc3-42ef-944d-04d7b1699980\",\n    \"project_id\": \"c6fd0474-19f1-4223-b6a9-752077c51d3d\",\n    \"scan_type\": \"feature_scout\",\n    \"category\": \"functionality\",\n    \"title\": \"Per-persona metrics breakdown in daily_metrics\",\n    \"description\": \"Extend the daily_metrics table with an optional persona_id column (NULL for aggregate rows). During the retention watermark rollup in retention.ts, group executions by persona_id in addition to date, writing per-persona rows alongside the existing aggregate. The metrics API can then support ?personaId= filtering. Requires a schema migration adding the column and updating the PRIMARY KEY to (date, persona_id).\",\n    \"reasoning\": \"Inspired by AWS Lambda per-function metrics and Vercel per-project analytics. Current daily_metrics only show aggregate totals, making it impossible to identify which persona drives cost or failures. Per-persona breakdown enables cost attribution — a critical feature for multi-persona deployments where one noisy persona can dominate spend.\",\n    \"effort\": 5,\n    \"impact\": 8,\n    \"risk\": 4\n  }'","description":"Save idea 3: Per-persona metrics"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":923,"cache_read_input_tokens":62743,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":923},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"637eb800-1367-4262-ba14-f65a42727d0a","uuid":"e7d3a997-99c0-4c40-95f8-620f49c80e1f"}
[2026-03-18T18:27:50.411Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01YCWExaCwkjM2DAYaZ947MJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_015cGzS5ebqLQSLFMDZ7fi3Y","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/ideas \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"scan_id\": \"1482c057-2bc3-42ef-944d-04d7b1699980\",\n    \"project_id\": \"c6fd0474-19f1-4223-b6a9-752077c51d3d\",\n    \"scan_type\": \"feature_scout\",\n    \"category\": \"functionality\",\n    \"title\": \"Per-tenant configurable retention windows\",\n    \"description\": \"Add a tenant_settings table (or column in tenants) storing per-tenant retention_days overrides. In runRetention, read the tenant-specific window before purging instead of using the global retentionDays config. Expose PUT /api/settings with retentionDays field scoped to the authenticated tenant. Falls back to global config when no override is set.\",\n    \"reasoning\": \"Inspired by AWS S3 lifecycle policies and Splunk index-level retention. Currently all tenants share the same global retentionDays (default 30). Enterprise customers often need longer retention for compliance while dev tenants want aggressive cleanup. Without per-tenant control, operators must choose a one-size-fits-all window that satisfies the most demanding tenant, wasting disk for everyone else.\",\n    \"effort\": 4,\n    \"impact\": 7,\n    \"risk\": 3\n  }'","description":"Save idea 4: Per-tenant retention"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":923,"cache_read_input_tokens":62743,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":923},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"637eb800-1367-4262-ba14-f65a42727d0a","uuid":"a0d3a103-feb7-48