e_scout\",\"category\":\"functionality\",\"title\":\"Per-persona metrics breakdown in daily_metrics\",\"description\":\"Extend the daily_metrics table with an optional persona_id column (NULL for aggregate rows). During the retention watermark rollup in retention.ts, group executions by persona_id in addition to date, writing per-persona rows alongside the existing aggregate. The metrics API can then support ?personaId= filtering. Requires a schema migration adding the column and updating the PRIMARY KEY to (date, persona_id).\",\"reasoning\":\"Inspired by AWS Lambda per-function metrics and Vercel per-project analytics. Current daily_metrics only show aggregate totals, making it impossible to identify which persona drives cost or failures. Per-persona breakdown enables cost attribution � a critical feature for multi-persona deployments where one noisy persona can dominate spend.\",\"status\":\"pending\",\"user_feedback\":null,\"user_pattern\":0,\"effort\":5,\"impact\":8,\"implemented_at\":null,\"created_at\":\"2026-03-18T18:27:50.378Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-18T18:27:50.378Z\",\"requirement_id\":null,\"goal_id\":null,\"risk\":4,\"provider\":null,\"model\":null,\"detailed\":0}}","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
[2026-03-18T18:27:52.903Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01YCWExaCwkjM2DAYaZ947MJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01PKPzohAmbHGCoQWYtZUmEu","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/ideas \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"scan_id\": \"1482c057-2bc3-42ef-944d-04d7b1699980\",\n    \"project_id\": \"c6fd0474-19f1-4223-b6a9-752077c51d3d\",\n    \"scan_type\": \"feature_scout\",\n    \"category\": \"user_benefit\",\n    \"title\": \"Cost anomaly detection with threshold alerts\",\n    \"description\": \"Extend the daily metrics aggregation in retention.ts to compute a rolling 7-day average cost per tenant. After aggregation, compare today cost against the rolling average; if it exceeds a configurable multiplier threshold (e.g. 2x), emit a structured log warning and optionally publish a system event. The threshold is configured via COST_ANOMALY_THRESHOLD env var. Uses existing daily_metrics data so no new data collection is needed.\",\n    \"reasoning\": \"Inspired by AWS Cost Anomaly Detection and GCP budget alerts. AI execution costs can spike unexpectedly from runaway prompts, infinite tool loops, or misconfigured personas. Without anomaly detection, operators only discover cost spikes after the damage is done. Early warning prevents bill shock — a critical user-trust feature for any platform billing for AI API calls.\",\n    \"effort\": 4,\n    \"impact\": 7,\n    \"risk\": 3\n  }'","description":"Save idea 5: Cost anomaly detection"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":923,"cache_read_input_tokens":62743,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":923},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"637eb800-1367-4262-ba14-f65a42727d0a","uuid":"ea6bc9fc-5d6f-4176-885a-1cc447225421"}
